<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JAN 94 / India eases mining curbs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW DELHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
India has decided as part of its economic reform programme to open the
state-owned mining industry wider to foreign and (domestic private
companies, Reuter reports from New Delhi.
United News of India said that the government issued an ordinance to allow
foreign investment in mining firms and lift restrictions on foreign equity
holding.
The ordinance would permit any company registered in India, irrespective of
its foreign equity holding, to apply for a mining lease or prospecting
license. Earlier laws restricted foreign equity in these companies to 40 per
cent.
