<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PLA, the Dutch holding company, has sold half of its 6m shareholding in IWP,
the Irish industrial holding company, in a deal estimated to be worth some
IPounds 12m (Pounds 11.5m).
The shares were acquired by PLA in November last year as part of a complex
IPounds 51m acquisition by IWP of Levendaal Beheer, a PLA subsidiary, in
