FT  26 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Cantors advances to Pounds 563,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Improved trading and tight control of overheads and margins enabled Cantors,
the furniture retailer, to report profits ahead from Pounds 175,000 to
Pounds 563,000 in the 26 weeks to October 23.
However, Mr Harold Cantor, chairman, said that trading in the second half
had been difficult, affected by the uncertainty created by the November
Budget.
He added that new year sales had started well and if the trend continued
there would be an acceptable improvement in full year profits.
Mr Cantor said that the experimental format of trading in retail parks was
continuing satisfactorily. One was opened in the period under review with
two more in December. Three more are planned before the end of the financial
year.
The shares rose 10p to 340p.
Turnover rose by 4 per cent from Pounds 28.7m to Pounds 29.8m. Trading
profit was almost doubled at Pounds 656,000 (Pounds 336,000). The pre-tax
result was helped by lower net interest charges of Pounds 93,000 (Pounds
161,000).
Earnings per share came out at 2.42p (0.76p). The interim dividend is
maintained at 1p.
