in Mozambique's first elections next October does not cheer spirits either.
The rebel group Renamo - once described as Africa's answer to the Khmer
Rouge - is busily acquiring the trappings of a conventional political party.
It has opened a sumptuous HQ in Maputo and spent Dollars 100,000 of UN money
on furnishings.
