<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JAN 94 / Backing for lower age of consent
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The prospect that the House of Commons may lower the age of consent for
homosexuals has increased significantly after a decision by Mr Michael
Howard, the home secretary, to back calls for it to be reduced from 21 to
18.
Mr Howard's decision to join a majority of the cabinet in supporting any
amendment proposing 18 may swing a number of rightwing Tory MPs in favour of
the change in next month's free Commons vote on the issue.
But the home secretary has told colleagues that he will strongly oppose a
reduction to 16 to align it with that for heterosexual sex. If no amendment
is tabled in favour of 18 Mr Howard will back maintenance of the present age
limit.
Mrs Edwina Currie, the backbench Tory MP, has tabled an amendment lowering
the age to 16, which has won the support of Mr John Smith, the Labour
leader.
