FT  26 JAN 94 / World News in Brief: Governors back 'ballet ban' head
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Governors of Kingsmead primary school, east London, decided not to suspend
headteacher Jane Brown, who had refused to let her pupils see the ballet
Romeo and Juliet because it was 'blatantly heterosexual'. Their decision
went against the recommendation of Hackney Council's director of education.
