corresponding period in the previous year, and are positive unless
otherwise stated. All growth rates refer to the seasonally adjusted
series except for Japan and Italy. German monetary statistics now form
a continuous pan-German series. Monetary data supplied by Datastream
and WEFA from central bank sources. Interest rates: short-term, period
averages of US - 90-day commercial paper, Japan - 3-month certificates
