<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JAN 94 / International Company News: MIM to shed Granges holding
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MIM, the Queensland-based metals group, has told Granges, the
Vancouver-based gold and base metals mining group, that it plans to sell its
37 per cent holding for not less than CDollars 4 a share, writes Nikki Tait.
At that price the sale would raise around CDollars 50m (USDollars 38m) for
MIM which, the Australian company indicated yesterday, would mean a small
capital loss. The Granges stake is currently carried on MIM's balance sheet
at ADollars 61.8m.
MIM shares eased 5 cents to ADollars 2.74 on the news.
</TEXT>
