FT  25 JAN 94 / UK Company News: British Bloodstock cuts loss to Pounds
0.21m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Reduced pre-tax losses of Pounds 213,000 were reported by The British
Bloodstock Agency for the half year to September 30, largely as a result of
the continuing cost reduction programme. Losses last time were Pounds
311,000.
Gross revenue fell to Pounds 7.76m (Pounds 9.99m) while turnover rose to
Pounds 1.76m (Pounds 1.67m). Losses per share were cut to 5.5p (8.1p).
Mr Christo Philipson, chairman, said the bloodstock market was
strengthening. However, he did not expect any dramatic improvement in
results, largely because of the erosion in margins resulting from increased
competition.
The USM-traded company is principally involved with the purchase and sale,
as agents, of bloodstock, stallion shares and nominations, as well as the
management, insurance and shipping of bloodstock.
